text.section:
Best management practices may include the following:
Practices designed to measure the amount of water conveyed through the system's infrastructure to water users, such as universal metering;
Audits of large-volume users;
Reuse and recycling of water for nonpotable, nonresidential applications;
Management of system pressure to reduce usage;
Retrofit programs;
Efficiency in landscape design and irrigation techniques;
Wastewater reclamation and recycling programs;
Fixture replacement programs;
Water and wastewater pricing structures that encourage improved efficiency;
Rebates and other financial incentives;
An education program for users designed to promote increased efficiency and conservation; and
Promotion or adoption of local water-use ordinances that encourage water conservation.
